{
  "texts": [
    "Medical imaging refers to the techniques and technologies used to produce visual representations of the interior of a body.",
    "In recent years, it has been widely applied to healthcare.",
    "It plays a significant role in modern medicine and is used in almost every aspect of patient care, such as diagnosis, therapy, and surgery.",
    "It helps clinicians identify and pinpoint disease progressions more precisely.",
    "Numerous imaging modalities have been utilized to detect and analyze lung diseases, including chest X-rays [3], CT scans [6], MRI [7], PET [6], sputum smear microscopy images (SSMI) [8], and molecular imaging [9]."
  ]
}